With JIRA 4.3 we can now have multiple directories, but if we wish to remove a user from one directory (say j.bloggs from the internal directory) but leave his issues as they are so that he can access them when authenticated through an external directory like LDAP, we are unable to do so. Either way, it will ask us to re-assign any issues before deleting the user, and even then will possibly delete the user from the wrong directory.

It would be great if we could see what directories a user can be found in and delete from a specific one only, and without removing links to issues if the user is present in another directory.

