When you go to Administration > Issue Settings > Issue Types > Edit (any issue type) > enter r e.g /images/icons OR  http://. The image is not saved among the default icons that come with JIRA. Even when JIRA is restarted these images do not appear. It would be nice if the users did not have to retype the /images/icons OR  http:// for images that they have already associated with an issue type. 

The improvement would then be to have any image that is added to the icon list be saved and included among the default icons for further use.

*Steps to reproduce*
# Click on {{Administration >> System >> Services}}
# Create a new service with the class 'com.atlassian.jira.service.services.file.FileService'
# In the *Instruction*, there is the following line (see screenshot: fileservice.png):
{noformat}
This service will retrieve data from [jira.home]/mail/ 
{noformat}

Since JIRA 4.2 onwards, the directory has been changed to [jira.home]/import/mail/

